Globacom Limited has said its international calling bundles allow subscribers to enjoy high-quality international calls at competitive prices. The company, in a statement, noted that customers could subscribe to its International Direct Dialling bundles for international calls via E-Top Up channels and Direct Recharge, which it said were available for existing and new prepaid subscribers. The statement read, “For the Direct Recharge option, the customer is required to dial *605*recharge PIN#, while the E-Top Up can be made via electronic channels such as bank USSD codes, bank ATMs, mobile banking applications, online/web payment platforms and point-of-sale terminals. “Subscribers can also buy the Glo IDD bundles by dialing *777# or through the Glo Café app. Glo IDD bundles include the N100 pack for nine minutes with three days’ validity, the N200 for 19 minutes with seven days’ validity, N500 for 43 minutes with 14 days’ validity and N1,000 bundle, which is for 93 minutes and valid for 30 days. “The bundles can be used to call popular destinations such as the United Kingdom, USA, Canada, China, India, Ireland, Malaysia, Singapore, Porto Rico, South Korea, Israel, Romania, Denmark, Mexico, Luxembourg, Magnolia and Norway.” 